snippet.textDisplay: Sounds like my dad (rip) he was in the country/bluegrass music seen with his brothers and sisters from the 60-90s in Nashville. He drunk himself to death with the help of pain killers. Its wasn't ruled a suicide, but I can relate to everything in this song watching him kill himself. My dad had raw talent with any instrument, my grandpa would knock his gitar out of tune before going back to work and he could get it back in tune at 4 years old. He has done shows with Loretta Lynn, Bill Monroe and more. No matter how much money he had, it was never enough. He was happy when my cousin David Weathers made it to the major leagues, my dad was a big baseball fan. Hell now David retired after 19 years and now his 20 year old son Ryan Weathers got drafted by the San Diego Padres. Anyway man.. fame doesnt make you happy, money doesnt make you happy. Only God can fill that gap in our life and yes my dad gave me shit for listen to rap music even then lol. NWA and Run DMC was the shit!!

snippet.textDisplay: Jelly roll I know this song hits many in so many ways. The passion and feelings you put into this is mind blowing. I cant get back the pieces their just feelings that fall to the ground. We are all victims of our own circumstances. I hope you get everything you deserve. Your music is straight therapy for the soul. Real talk.
